Wushu Salad

3 tablespoons rice vinegar
½ cup roasted sesame oil
½ cup peanut oil
1 teaspoon sugar
1 teaspoon chicken bouillon
salt
black pepper
1 package dry ramen, crumbled
1 green cabbage, chopped
2 green onions, diced
2 cups cooked chicken, chopped

Makes eight bowls of salad.

Mix vinegar, oils, sugar, bouillon and salt and pepper to taste in a small bowl. In a large bowl, combine ramen, cabbage, onions and chicken. Add liquid mixture to large bowl and mix well. Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.

Serve chilled sprinkled with furikake.
